in greater spending or perhaps

32
00:02:03,670 --> 00:02:06,130
a greater likelihood of donation.

33
00:02:06,130 --> 00:02:10,929
Likewise, in a sunk cost setting, increasing
the amount that people

34
00:02:10,929 --> 00:02:15,769
prepay for a basketball game ticket increases
the likelihood that they

35
00:02:15,769 --> 00:02:18,870
will fall prey to the sunk cost effect.

36
00:02:18,870 --> 00:02:23,680
In this case, the framing of the price as
pennies a day or the dollars that

37
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:28,670
are spent in prepaying for a given ticket
are the cause, while the

38
00:02:28,670 --> 00:02:32,049
greater spending that occurs as a result,
or the greater sunk cost

39
00:02:32,049 --> 00:02:37,790
effect that occurs as a result, will be the
effect.

40
00:02:37,790 --> 00:02:40,209
Let's focus a minute on the pennies a day.

41
00:02:40,209 --> 00:02:44,779
The idea behind the pennies a day research
