spend on that product or service.

44
00:02:55,159 --> 00:02:57,769
Why does this happen?

45
00:02:57,769 --> 00:03:01,739
John Gourville's work suggested that when
a price is framed as a pennies a

46
00:03:01,739 --> 00:03:07,019
day price, it increases the perception of
affordability of the product,

47
00:03:07,019 --> 00:03:10,840
thereby resulting in greater spending.

48
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:16,139
This intermediate variable between the cause
and the effect is often called a

49
00:03:16,139 --> 00:03:18,630
mediating variable.

50
00:03:18,630 --> 00:03:24,819
So in this case, the cause results in the
mediator, which in turn results in

51
00:03:24,819 --> 00:03:30,659
the effect of interest, i.e.
pennies a day changes the perception of affordability,

52
00:03:30,659 --> 00:03:36,120
which itself results
